      <div xml:id="NA230-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi vāyiṉ maṟuttatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante refuses the door.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA230">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            muyappiṭic ceviyi ṉaṉṉa pācaṭaik</l>
<l>            kayakkaṇak kokki ṉaṉṉa kūmpumukai</l>
<l>            kaṇaikkā lāmpa lamiḻtunāṟu taṇpōtu</l>
<l>            kuṇakkuttōṉṟu veḷḷiyi ṉiruḷkeṭa viriyuṅ</l>
<l>            kayaṟkaṇaṅ kalitta poykai yūra </l>
<l>            muṉivil parattaiyai yeṟṟuṟan taruḷāy</l>
<l>            naṉipulam palaitta vēlai nīṅkap</l>
<l>            putuvaṟaṅ kūrnta ceṟuviṟ ṟaṇṇeṉa</l>
<l>            malipuṉal parattan tāaṅ</l>
<l>            kiṉitē teyyaniṟ kāṇuṅ kālē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from a village with a pond where the carps have been flourishing,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the ambrosia-scented cool buds of the round-stemmed</l>
<l rend="indent">white waterlily,</l>
<l rend="indent3">closing buds, like herons in groups in a pond,</l>
<l rend="indent3">green leaves as the ear of the ...(?) female elephant,</l>
<l rend="indent">expand themselves to dispel the darkness like Venus appearing to the east,</l>
<l rend="indent4">– having another woman without dislike [for you],</l>
<l>you have abandoned me without consideration.</l>
<l>Pleasant is the time of seeing you,</l>
<l rend="indent">as if an abundant flood were to spread, [bringing] coolness,</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the fields abounding in new drought,</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that summer(?) leaves that had afflicted [them] with much loneliness.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
